						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rajendra II. Year 7: A.D. 1039.</hi></p>						

						<p>Gift of two lamps by Tiruveṇkāṭṭu Naṅgai from Chembiyaṉ-kuḍavāyil <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Ālampālil to the temple of Tirumayāṉam Uḍaiyar at Nālūr, in Chēṟṟūr-kūṟṟam, a subdivision of Kulōttuṅgachōḻa-vaḷanāḍu. The <hi rend="italic">śivabrāhmaṇas</hi> of the temple undertook to maintain lamps.</p>						

